<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Soviet envoy Yuli M. Vorontsov arrived in Pakistan for a visit expected to 
include talks with Afghan guerrilla leaders. Vorontsov indicated that Moscow's 
troop withdrawal from Afghanistan will proceed on schedule if there are no 
further rebel attacks. Under accords signed last April in Geneva, all Soviet 
troops are to be withdrawn by Feb. 15. Vorontsov, one of Moscow's top 
diplomatic trouble-shooters, arrived in Islamabad from Tehran, where he spoke 
with Iranian-based Afghan resistance leaders. 
</P>
