<HEADLINE>
<P>
NICHOLAS CALAS; POET AND ART CRITIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nicholas Calas, 81, a poet and art critic whose work focused on young artists 
and new art movements. Calas contributed to Art Forum, Arts Magazine, Art 
International and other journals. Many of his essays on the deeper cultural 
meanings of modern art were collected in "Art in the Age of Risk." Calas 
collaborated with anthropologist Margaret Mead on "Primitive Heritage," a 1953 
anthology of texts chosen for their literary and humanistic significance. In 
New York City on Saturday of heart failure. 
</P>
