<HEADLINE>
<P>
THOMAS GUINNESS; FORMER AVIATOR, MEMBER OF PARLIAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
British businessman Thomas Loel Evelyn Bulkeley Guinness, 82, a former aviator 
and member of Parliament. Guinness, whose family made its fortune in banking 
and is related to the Guinness brewery dynasty, was a member of the House of 
Commons from 1931 to 1945. One of the first people in Britain to own an 
airplane, Guinness commanded a squadron of fighter planes during World War II, 
and in 1944 was promoted to wing commander. After the war, he inherited a large 
fortune from his father and for a time was president of the former British 
United Airways. In a Houston hospital on Saturday after suffering a heart 
attack at his Acapulco, Mexico, home on Friday. 
</P>
