<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 38-year-old woman was injured Wednesday morning on Interstate 5 when her car 
collided with a school bus while changing lanes, the California Highway Patrol 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
The motorist, Lilia Ciballos, of San Diego was northbound on the freeway, just 
south of Interstate 8, when her car was hit on the left side by the bus. She 
was taken to UC San Diego Medical Center, where she underwent surgery for 
treatment of leg injuries. 
</P>
<P>
None of the children on the bus were injuried. 
</P>
</TEXT>
