<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEPPERDINE PLAYS HOST TO BOISE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RAY RIPTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pepperdine, coming off a 102-80 loss at home to sixth-ranked North Carolina 
Tuesday night, will play host to Boise State at 7:30 tonight at Firestone 
Fieldhouse in Malibu. 
</P>
<P>
The Waves have an 8-6 record. 
</P>
<P>
Boise State (8-1), the defending Big Sky Conference champion, won last season's 
conference tournament and advanced to the second round of the National 
Invitation Tournament. The Broncos are coached by Bobby Dye, former coach at 
Cerritos and Santa Monica community colleges, Cal State Fullerton and Cal State 
Bakersfield. 
</P>
<P>
Dye's team has been holding opponents to an average of 58 points a game. Boise 
State is led by 6-foot 3-inch forward Wilson Foster, who is averaging 13.6 
points a game, and by two-time all-conference guard Chris Childs, who is 
averaging 13 points and nearly 5 assists. RAY RIPTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
