MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
And a dozen major public television stations have received $100.5 million in 
underwriting commitments for current and future programs. The funding is mostly 
from corporations and foundations, topped by a five-year, $57-million 
underwriting of "The MacNeil/Lehrer NewsHour" by AT&amp;T, Pepsico and the John 
D. and Catherine T. MacArthur Foundation. Corporations aren't the only ones 
writing checks. PBS further reports that December membership drives netted 
individual pledges totaling a record $18.4 million, up 14.4% from last year. 
