SAN DIEGO SPOTLIGHT: SAN DIEGO ENTERTAINMENT BRIEFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The International Orchestra of USIU will present its Friday night concert at 
the Lyceum Theatre as a benefit for victims and survivors of the earthquake in 
Soviet Armenia. To augment proceeds from the performance, donations from 
concert-goers will be accepted by representatives of the St. John Armenian 
Apostolic Church. San Diego Mayor O'Connor has proclaimed Jan. 6, which is also 
the day Christmas is celebrated on the Armenian calendar, as International 
Orchestra of USIU day. The concert opens the university orchestra's downtown 
"Mozart Plus" series. 
