<P>
DIGEST: DOWNEY; 
</P>
<P>
CAR DEALER GETS DELAY IN MEETING SIGN LAW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Downey City Council has approved a zoning variance allowing Paramount 
Chevrolet to retain three of its pole signs until June, 1990. The 18-month 
period will allow the car dealership time to comply with the city's zoning 
ordinance for store advertisements enacted under the city's redevelopment 
program. The current signs violate size and height restrictions. The 
dealership, located at Paramount and Firestone boulevards, has been in Downey 
for nearly 50 years. 
</P>
