<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: SOUTH PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
POLL ON TAXES FOR SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Searching for ways to solve the school district's financial problems, a 
22-member citizens panel this month will conduct a poll of residents about 
their attitudes regarding new taxes. 
</P>
<P>
The Financial Strategy Planning Committee will employ the firm of Fairbank, 
Bregman &amp; Maullin, with offices in Santa Monica and San Francisco, to 
conduct the telephone survey, which will be paid for from private fund-raising 
activities, a spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The 5-school district, which recently agreed to a 10% raise in teachers' 
salaries, was forced to eliminate $750,000 in budget items to close a budget 
gap for the school year. Greater budget shortfalls are expected next year. The 
panel, which was established last month by the school board, has discussed 
asking voters for a special parcel tax to increase the school budget. It has 
also reportedly considered a bond issue for capital expenses, which would 
require voter approval. 
</P>
</TEXT>
