<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: SAN MARINO; 
</P>
<P>
SCHOOL BOARD PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
David Destino, a lawyer, has been elected president of the San Marino Board of 
Education. Other officers who were elected at a special meeting of the board in 
December are Debby Bowes, vice president, and Mary Snaer, clerk. Destino 
succeeds Selma Sax, who was board president for two years. 
</P>
