<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAISES FOR CITY DEPARTMENT HEADS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Times researcher Cecilia Rasmussen 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pay raises of 4% for "satisfactory," 6% for "fully satisfactory" and 7% for 
"superior" job performance were approved Wednesday by the Los Angeles City 
Council for city department heads. The raises, which are retroactive to July 1, 
1988, will cost taxpayers about $200,000. 
</P>
