</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SUSPECT CHARGED IN 2ND OF 13 HOLDUPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man arrested as a suspect in a string of 10 armored car and three bank 
holdups in the past year was formally charged Wednesday with a second one of 
the robberies. 
</P>
<P>
Steven Bernard Young, 29, was charged by the district attorney's office with 
the $166,000 holdup of an armored car guard at the Cineplex Odeon movie complex 
Nov. 26 in Universal City. An alleged accomplice remains at large. 
</P>
<P>
Young is scheduled to be arraigned today in Municipal Court. He was charged 
last week with the $180,000 holdup of an armored car Sept. 16 outside a Los 
Angeles supermarket. 
</P>
<P>
Prosecutors are reviewing the other holdups to determine whether Young will be 
formally charged in those crimes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
