<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHO'S HOT / WHO'S NOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Loyola Marymount forward Hank Gathers scored 39 and 49 points in two victories 
to earn West Coast Athletic Conference and Sports Illustrated Player of the 
Week honors. The 6-7 junior tied a school record with 49 points against Reno 
and had 26 rebounds. Gathers is averaging 34.4 points and 14.1 rebounds a game, 
ranking among the nation's leaders in both categories. 
</P>
<P>
Redondo boasted the South Bay's hottest prep basketball program last week as 
the varsity, junior varsity and freshman teams reached the finals of 
tournaments. The varsity and JV lost in the finals of the Nogales and Redondo 
tournaments while the freshmen won at Palos Verdes. 
</P>
<P>
Rolling Hills forward John Hardy was the leading scorer and rebounder at the 
30-team Las Vegas Holiday Basketball Classic, averaging 32.8 points and 12.3 
boards in four games. 
</P>
<P>
Who's Not 
</P>
<P>
Bishop Montgomery's basketball team scored only nine points in the second half, 
including a paltry two in the third quarter, to squander a 23-18 halftime lead 
and lose to Mira Costa, 47-32, last Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The Cal State Dominguez Hills basketball team failed to verify its flight time 
to Seattle for the Puget Sound Tournament and missed a connecting flight in San 
Jose. The Toros split into two groups, boarded separate flights, and arrived at 
Puget Sound half an hour before game time Thursday and lost to Central 
Washington, 61-52. 
</P>
<P>
Chadwick lost both of its games in the Bishop Union Basketball Tournament to 
fall to 2-9, the Dolphins' worst start under longtime Coach Tom Maier. 
</P>
<P>
Banning's basketball team had a rough week, losing its three games in the 
Glendale Tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
