<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
BOARD VOTES TO BOOST TRASH COLLECTION FEES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Board of Supervisors voted unanimously Wednesday to increase rubbish 
collection fees in unincorporated areas of the county by about 13% for most 
homeowners and 10% for commercial users. 
</P>
<P>
At present, rubbish collection rates range from $6.38 to $7.17 per month for 
residences in unincorporated Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
In the communities of Laguna Niguel, El Toro, Dana Point and Lake Forest, the 
fee will increase from $6.90 to $7.80 per month, effective Jan. 1. For 
commercial users in those areas, the fee is increasing from $49.83 to $54.81 
per month. 
</P>
<P>
The range of commercial rates throughout unincorporated Orange County has been 
from $42.49 to $67.68. 
</P>
<P>
R.A. Scott, director of the county's General Services Agency, said the 
increased fees are consistent with those of other cities and counties in 
Southern California. He said the increase is based on a rise in the Consumer 
Price Index. 
</P>
<P>
The last increase in rubbish collection fees was 6% in January, 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
