<P>
OCEAN VIEW HOLDS OFF LONG BEACH POLY, 73-61 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Todd Norman scored 26 points and Mike Frohn 21 as Ocean View High School 
defeated Long Beach Poly, 73-61, Wednesday in a nonleague boys' basketball game 
at Ocean View. 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View (10-3) went on top early and led, 18-4, late in the first quarter. 
Long Beach Poly rallied and closed to within 30-26 at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach Poly got within 1 late in the third quarter and trailed by only 4 
entering the final quarter. However, the Seahawks made 10 of 12 free throws 
down the stretch to pull away. 
</P>
<P>
Norman had 12 rebounds and Frohn 6. 
</P>
<P>
In other nonleague games: 
</P>
<P>
Edison 55, Long Beach Wilson 41 -- Bill Martineau scored 16 points and Bryan 
Murphy 13 to lead host Edison (7-9). The Chargers trailed, 27-22, at halftime 
but outscored Long Beach Wilson, 33-14, in the second half. Martineau scored 12 
points and Murphy 9 in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
Estancia 89, Costa Mesa 44 -- Estancia made 65 percent of its shots from the 
field at Costa Mesa. The Eagles (12-1) led, 31-8, at the end of the first 
quarter and, 44-14, at halftime. Mike Curtis scored 22 points and Tim Kjar 17 
for Estancia. Tim Nguyen scored 21 points for Costa Mesa. 
