<TEXT>
<P>
Last season, the Kennedy High School boys' soccer team dominated every team in 
the Garden Grove League with one exception: Bolsa Grande. 
</P>
<P>
The Matadors were the only blemishes on Kennedy's 12-1-1 league record last 
season. On Wednesday, the Fighting Irish extracted a little revenge. 
</P>
<P>
Mark Florek and Diego Abbes each scored twice as Kennedy routed the Matadors, 
5-1, in a league match at Bolsa Grande. Last season, the Matadors beat the 
Fighting Irish, 3-1, and tied them, 3-3. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy is 3-3-2 overall, 2-0 in league play. 
</P>
